 According to a statement issued by the Mpumalanga Department of Community Safety, Security and Liaison the accident occurred when a truck and a minibus were involved in a “side swipe collision” at around 04:00 today (Friday 14 June). The impact caused the minibus to overturn. Four people were declared dead on the scene whilst four were transported to hospital with serious injuries and another eight sustained slight injuries. The minibus carried 16 people.  According to Moeti Mmusi, spokesperson for the department, the occupants in the minibus are believed to have been travelling from the Eastern Cape to Moria in Limpopo for religious purposes. Communuty Safety, Security and Liaison MEC Gabisile Shabalala raised concerns about the high death toll on the N11.
“We are worried about (the) N11 Road in Middelburg as it continues to claim many people’s lives,” she said.     More fatalities after bus accident on Stoffberg road Municipality makes gruesome discovery in blocked drain Horrific accident: Ten casualties airlifted to Mpumalanga hospitals VIDEO – Peeing in public, a nuisance of note • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za 